⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Noah Wilder
node LMZ · LMZ · ⟦Noah Wilder:LMZ:a525ea⟧

WHO   — Noah Wilder — the boy who builds the bridge
WHAT  — Curiosity made capable: a normal kid whose mind the toys race years ahead, until he can construct a portal to the future out of wonder.
WHERE — LMZ · The Last Mimzy (2007)  Framework inputs: The Last Mimzy (2007, dir. Robert Shaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film needs to show that the toys teach by play, not force — and Noah is play turned into engineering.
HOW   — By absorbing the toys' lessons into sudden genius and building the bridge that sends Mimzy home.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Last month I could barely do my science fair. Then I could teleport a marble, talk to spiders, and build a door to the future.

